'''Benedikte Shetelig Kruse''' (born 20 December 1979 in [[Oslo, Norway]]) is a Norwegian [[singer]] and [[actor]], daughter of Professor of music, Gro Shetelig Kruse, and the [[Composer]] [[Bjørn Kruse]]. She is the sister of actress and singers [[Jannike Kruse|Jannike]] and [[Anine Kruse]].

== Career ==
Kruse studied music at the [[Foss videregående skole]], and is a graduated [[singer]] and [[singing teacher]] from the [[Norwegian Academy of Music]], with experience from [[theater]] and [[television]]. She has worked with educational music programs for children and youth together with [[Anja Eline Skybakmoen]]. In 2004 together with [[Ane Carmen Roggen]], she sang the choir on the record ''[[Nomadesongar]]'' with [[Lars Klevstrand]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.korbanken.no/korovelsen/vel-forberedt/kor-som-sv |title=Korbanken - Skattekiste for barne- og ungdomskor |language=Norwegian |publisher=Korbanken.no |accessdate=2014-04-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121228213911/http://www.korbanken.no/korovelsen/vel-forberedt/kor-som-sv |archivedate=28 December 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

Together with her sister [[Anine Kruse]], [[Anja Eline Skybakmoen]], [[Ane Carmen Roggen]] and [[Ida Roggen]] she comprises the vocal group [[Pitsj]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pitsj.no |title=Pitsj - Offisielt nettsted |publisher=Pitsj.no |accessdate=2014-04-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111202181840/http://www.pitsj.no/ |archive-date=2 December 2011 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> and has also done many dubbing jobs. In 2011 she performed the Show Pitsj & Gumbo at the [[Oslo Concert Hall]], where "A capella møter en hot New Orleans-rett" (A capella meets a hot New Orleans Dish).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oblad.no/folloliv/musikalsk-nyttarsfeiring-1.8242629 |title=Pitsj & Gumbo |publisher=OsloKonserthus.no |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

In January 2014, the Kruse sisters celebrated music with a New Year Show, getting excellent recipient in the local press.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oslokonserthus.no/action/displayArticle?aid=3228 |title=Musikalsk nyttårsfeiring |language=Norwegian |first=Daniel |last=Gauslaa |publisher=[[Østlandets Blad]] |date=2014-01-13 |accessdate=2014-04-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427195519/http://www.oslokonserthus.no/action/displayArticle?aid=3228 |archivedate=27 April 2014 |df=dmy }}</ref>

== Discography ==
*1992: ''Wenches Jul'' (CNR Records), with [[Wenche Myhre]]
*2004: ''[[Nomadesongar]]'' (Tylden & Co), with [[Lars Klevstrand]]
*2005: ''Distant Shores'' (Everyday Records), with Trond Teigen'
*2005: ''Rain'' (Everyday Records), with [[Paal Flaata]]
*2006: ''[[Pitsj (album)|Pitsj]]'' ([[Grappa Music|Grappa]]), within [[Pitsj]]
*2009: ''[[Gjenfortellinger]]'' (Grappa), within Pitsj
*2009: ''Edvard Grieg in jazz mood'' (Universal Music, 2009), Pitsj with [[Kjell Karlsen]] ("I Dovregubbens hall")
*2009: ''Med Andre Ord'' (DnC), with [[Jannike Kruse]]
*2009: ''Autographs'' (EMC Classic), with Otto Graf
*2010: ''16 Sanger Til Maneten Medusa'' (Schmell), with Åshild Watne
*2014: ''Snow Is Falling'' (Grappa Music)

